songs.title: Good Enough
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1: Jesy]
I am the diamond you left in the dust
I am the future you lost in the past
Seems like I never compare
Wouldn't notice if I disappear
You stole the love that I saved for myself
And I watched you give it to somebody else
But these scars no longer I hide

[Pre-Chorus 1: Jesy]
I found the light you shut inside
Couldn't love me if you tried

[Chorus: Jesy]
Am I still not good enough?
Am I still not worth that much?
I'm sorry for the way my life turned out
Sorry for the smile I'm wearing now
Guess I'm still not good enough

[Verse 2: Leigh-Anne]
Does it burn knowing I used all the pain?
Does it hurt knowing you're fuel to my flame?
Don't look back, don't need your regrets

[Pre-Chorus 2: Leigh-Anne]
Thank God you left my love behind
Couldn't change me if you tried

[Chorus: Jade]
Am I still not good enough?
Am I still not worth that much?
I'm sorry for the way my life turned out
Sorry for the smile I'm wearing now, guess I'm still not good enough

[Bridge: Perrie]
Release your curse 'cause I know my worth
Those wounds you made are gone
You ain't seen nothing yet
Your love wore thin and I never win
You want the best, so sorry
That's clearly not me
Oh, this is all I can be

[Chorus: All]
Am I still not good enough?
Am I still not worth that much?
I'm sorry for the way my life turned out
Sorry for the smile I'm wearing now
Guess I'm still not good enough
